PORTS	{{.Ports}}
COMMAND	{{.Command}}
CREATED	{{.CreatedAt}}
STATUS	{{.Status}}
""ID	{{.ID}}
NAME	{{.Names}}
IMAGE	{{.Image}}
PORTS	{{.Ports}}
COMMAND	{{.Command}}
CREATED	{{.CreatedAt}}
STATUS	{{.Status}}
"

PowerSheel list all or one variable
> dir env:
> dir env:FORMAT
> $env:FORMAT

List containers based on a variable holding the format
> docker ps --format=$($env:FORMAT)

topLevelComment.text:
For windows User who are trying to display docker ps in beautiful format-

1. (set space FORMAT)
set FORMAT=ID	{{.ID}}
NAME	{{.Names}}
IMAGE	{{.Image}}
PORTS	{{.Ports}}
COMMAND	{{.Command}}
CREATED	{{.CreatedAt}}
STATUS	{{.Status}}


2. OPTIONAL NO NEED , JUST TO DISPLAY
echo %FORMAT%

o/p -ID	{{.ID}}
NAME	{{.Names}}
IMAGE	{{.Image}}
PORTS	{{.Ports}}
COMMAND	{{.Command}}
CREATED	{{.CreatedAt}}
STATUS	{{.Status}}


3.
docker ps --format=%FORMAT%

